Thomas B. Michaud


         Tom Michaud  has spent the last 25 years, his entire professional career, at Keefe, Bruyette  & Woods. He was named President & CEO in October, 2011, having served  as Vice Chairman and Chief Operating Officer since September, 2001. Tom remains  Vice Chairman of the Board of Directors.In 2004,  Tom led KBW’s successful expansion into Europe,  establishing a true international research, sales and trading franchise. He was  also instrumental in KBW’s expansion into Asia  in 2010.Prior to be  appointed CEO, under Tom’s leadership, KBW became one of the top five traders and  brokers of financial services stocks and has developed an industry leading  research effort. KBW has also emerged as the leading manager for small, mid and  large cap equity offerings in the financial services sector.Before  being named Vice Chairman and Chief Operating Officer in 2001, Tom was Director  of Sales and Executive Vice President. While leading this group, KBW’s equity  commission business grew by more than 25% per year, far outpacing the industry  average. He also helped oversee KBW’s transition from a bank-only boutique to a  financial services specialist, adding insurance, brokerage, real estate and  asset management practices.Mr. Michaud  Tom earned a B.A. in Economics from Middlebury  College and an M.B.A. from New York University’s Stern School of Business.  He currently serves on the Board of Advisors of the Greenwich, Connecticut  chapter of The American Red Cross and the Foreign Policy Association Board of  Directors.

     




















